Package: CONICSmat
Title: What the Package Does (one line, title case)
Version: 0.0.0.1
Authors@R: person("Soren", "Muller", email = "soeren.mueller@ucsf.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: CONICSmat is an R package for infering large-scale copy number variations (CNVs) from (single cell) RNA-sequencing data. CONICSmat utilizes gaussina mixture models to infer the copy number status of each sample in a set of regions provided by the user, or alternative for each chromosome. 
Depends: R (>= 3.3.0)
Imports:
    beanplot,
    mixtools,
    pheatmap,
    biomaRt,
	Rtsne,
	squash,
	scran
